<subSubSection id="B577FCE7D339767B884BC928CA400C66" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EF2F1EB180E21ECA45AD4B5D2CC202EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F27FD9501C572934B093BF691C001E95" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Head, pronotum, and elytra dark brown, with paler lateral portions of pronotum and elytra, legs yellow (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="44B245B0C4BE57BDF9866FDD46A47608" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Habitus of Pseudocsikia spp. A Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male holotype, dorsal view B Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male holotype, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691080" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">1A</figureCitation>
). Antennomere II subequal in length to antennomere III. Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="54C652610C0911620CEBDE61D5311D62" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Characters of Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male, holotype A pronorum, dorsal view B pro- and mesothorax, ventral view C anterior protrusion of pronotum, dorsal view D anterior protrusion of hypomeron, ventral view E antenna F posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view G metacoxal plate, ventral view H prosternal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, E, F); 0.2 mm (C, D, G, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691082" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">3A</figureCitation>
) smooth, with sparse punctures (intervals usually equal to 4-6 puncture diameters). Anterior angle of pronotum with apex of protrusion closer to inner angle. Posterior angles divergent. Metaventrite sparsely punctate, intervals between punctures on average subequal to 2-5 puncture diameters. Metacoxal plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FC524B97EDA090C15E36B3F55837075F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Characters of Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male, holotype A pronorum, dorsal view B pro- and mesothorax, ventral view C anterior protrusion of pronotum, dorsal view D anterior protrusion of hypomeron, ventral view E antenna F posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view G metacoxal plate, ventral view H prosternal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, E, F); 0.2 mm (C, D, G, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691082" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">3G</figureCitation>
) enlarged mesally, sparsely punctate. Tergite IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="18B6D89634620674D6B18A42D0975AA7" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Characters of Pseudocsikia spp. A-F Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male holotype G-L Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male, holotype A, G abdominal sternite IX, dorsal view B, H abdominal tergites IX-X, dorsal view C, I abdominal sternite VIII and tergite VIII, ventral view D, J aedeagus, ventral view E, K aedeagus, lateral view F, L aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691084" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5B</figureCitation>
) subtriangular, with two narrow lobes. Aedeagus with median lobe with acute lateral projetions near midlength, narrowed to apex, apex blunt with small acute lateral projections. Paramere with apex pointed and projecting laterad. Phallobase with basal angles rounded (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B1653DD774529E9FAE28DE45B0D060EB" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Characters of Pseudocsikia spp. A-F Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male holotype G-L Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male, holotype A, G abdominal sternite IX, dorsal view B, H abdominal tergites IX-X, dorsal view C, I abdominal sternite VIII and tergite VIII, ventral view D, J aedeagus, ventral view E, K aedeagus, lateral view F, L aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691084" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="1E237A38444D4C89B1213A5D6E0C44CF" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691081" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
